      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): prevent recursive task execution during model fallback",
        "body": "This PR fixes a critical hiearchical paradox in OpenClaw's fallback mechanism.\n\n### Problem\nWhen a session falls back to a model using a **CLI Runtime** (e.g., Gemini CLI), the model often boots with a 'subordinate' persona from its specific workspace (e.g., 'You are the primary muscle'). Because it receives the full session history, it misinterprets previous task completions as new directives, leading to duplicate commits and corrupted PR states.\n\n### Solution\n1. Adds an `isFallback` flag to CLI runparams.\n2. Injects a clear **'Fallback Identity'** instruction into the system prompt when a fallback takes over.\n3. This instruction explicitly tells the model it is now acting as the **Lead Agent** and that history is its own, preventing recursive execution.\n\nVerified in a live session where Gemini was re-executing PR commands.\n\n\nFixes #92271\n",
        "branch": "fix/fallback-recursive-task-execution",
